{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"06e5f8b6-ed1d-4906-a6de-ba777d919247","title":"Chat Documents","desc":"","updated":1661886422548,"created":1615482779857,"custom":{},"fname":"projects.saga-tales","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"22c50452d8b88fab9374c2a354f7c140","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"projects.saga-tales","id":"06e5f8b6-ed1d-4906-a6de-ba777d919247","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"theory.subprojecting","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":42,"offset":177},"end":{"line":4,"column":66,"offset":201},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"theory.subprojecting"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"projects.saga-tales","id":"06e5f8b6-ed1d-4906-a6de-ba777d919247","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"rethinking-media.better-meetings","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":270,"offset":405},"end":{"line":4,"column":306,"offset":441},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"rethinking-media.better-meetings"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"projects.saga-tales","id":"06e5f8b6-ed1d-4906-a6de-ba777d919247","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"projects.chat-fs","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":106,"offset":1455},"end":{"line":21,"column":126,"offset":1475},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"projects.chat-fs"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"projects.saga-tales","id":"06e5f8b6-ed1d-4906-a6de-ba777d919247","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"projects.chat-fs","position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":15,"offset":1492},"end":{"line":23,"column":35,"offset":1512},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"projects.chat-fs"}}],"anchors":{"a-new-kind-of-document":{"type":"header","text":"A new kind of document","value":"a-new-kind-of-document","line":14,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"5988f8ec-c945-458a-8309-9f318af16602","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"chat-documents\">Chat Documents<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#chat-documents\"></a></h1>\n<p>For nearly a year I've been struggling to build a prototype, solo, what I outlined in <a href=\"https://a9.io/glue-comic\">Chatting with Glue</a>.</p>\n<p>So I'm making an intermediate prototype (<a href=\"/inquiry/notes/688f0aa8-338b-424e-abb2-d6067e7fae5e\">Downscoping as a skill (subprojecting)</a>) without the hard parts (privacy, authentication, notifications), using a lightweight realtime database. It'll resemble a chat app but will nominally be a collaborative outliner tool. For meeting notes (<a href=\"/inquiry/notes/1d0d9bf0-f059-476a-842a-0dc747ec2b85\">Better Meetings</a>) and such.</p>\n<p>Word processing and whiteboarding are the wrong metaphors for shared info accretion during a call. You're always worrying about layout and overwriting the other person's thoughts. Need atomicity.</p>\n<h2 id=\"a-new-kind-of-document\">A new kind of document<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#a-new-kind-of-document\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Why is this better than Slack etc?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Infinite threading, inline quotation/embellishment <em>does matter</em>, and it matters a ton. It's a whole other mode of thinking (hypothesis)</li>\n<li>Messages are more malleable/data-like when they're collapsible. Legible more as an outline, a document, a record\n<ul>\n<li>It doesn't replace Slack, it's another product category</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Let's find out if it is empirically!</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>What if each chat \"workspace\" originated with a chat message on the homescreen? The homescreen is a private scratchpad and you can share messages and their descendants with people.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Inline hashtags/mentions are crucial, with autocomplete for them to invite accretion</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Copy-paste handling needs to be next-level. Drag and drop. It should be as good as a finder window (a la <a href=\"/inquiry/notes/37OcxJWLvRCT3Q8qGB56Y\">ChatFS</a>)</p>\n<p>Related idea: <a href=\"/inquiry/notes/37OcxJWLvRCT3Q8qGB56Y\">ChatFS</a></p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://matrix.org/blog/2020/12/18/introducing-cerulean\">https://matrix.org/blog/2020/12/18/introducing-cerulean</a></strong></p>","noteIndex":{"id":"940ad93a-2b54-497e-ab18-335879950834","title":"Max's Inquiry","updated":1616115341623,"modified":"2022-08-26T16:46:41.000Z","desc":null,"custom":{"modified":"2022-08-26T16:46:41.000Z","nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"7936220386f369ace243d8e835153790","created":1695797153867,"links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"940ad93a-2b54-497e-ab18-335879950834","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"projects.linear-algebra-spreadsheet","alias":"Linear algebra as spreadsheet","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":3,"offset":949},"end":{"line":16,"column":72,"offset":1018},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"projects.linear-algebra-spreadsheet"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"940ad93a-2b54-497e-ab18-335879950834","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"rethinking-media.microworld-languages","alias":"Domain learning for computational microworlds","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":3,"offset":1021},"end":{"line":17,"column":90,"offset":1108},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"rethinking-media.microworld-languages"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"940ad93a-2b54-497e-ab18-335879950834","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"projects.linux-desktop","alias":"Linux DE prototyping","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":3,"offset":1111},"end":{"line":18,"column":50,"offset":1158},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"projects.linux-desktop"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"940ad93a-2b54-497e-ab18-335879950834","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"projects.system-archaeology","alias":"System Archaeology","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":3,"offset":1161},"end":{"line":19,"column":53,"offset":1211},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"projects.system-archaeology"}}],"anchors":{"guide":{"type":"header","text":"Guide","value":"guide","line":19,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["2e6e45b5-be90-4ef3-8720-6e52ce04cb9a","5988f8ec-c945-458a-8309-9f318af16602","86c66ea6-63bc-4711-8eff-13bb9260db4f","d8a51d81-83c8-45b4-84fa-9b55dce793ac"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"\nThis is [Max Krieger](https://a9.io)'s \"inquiry\" page. I guess it's like a [Digital Garden](https://github.com/MaggieAppleton/digital-gardeners). But I'm not trying to upload my Second Brain to it. Just want to share some half-baked ideas. One source of inspiration for this was Kevin Lynagh's [\"Collaboration ideas\"](https://kevinlynagh.com/ideas/). See also Sharif Shameem's [\"Questions\"](https://sharif.io/questions/).\n\nIt was made with [Dendron](https://dendron.so).\n\nTake everything I write here (well, everywhere) with a grain of salt. That said I'm always happy to talk about anything on here.\n\nThe pages definitely don't adhere to [Andy's Evergreen Notes](https://notes.andymatuschak.org/z4SDCZQeRo4xFEQ8H4qrSqd68ucpgE6LU155C) pattern, I hope one day they do.\n\nFeel free to add [a PR or issue to the repo](https://github.com/maxkrieger/inquiry) to discuss any of these in public!\n\n## Guide\n\nHere are some of my favorite/extensive pages:\n\n- [[Linear algebra as spreadsheet|projects.linear-algebra-spreadsheet]]\n- [[Domain learning for computational microworlds|rethinking-media.microworld-languages]]\n- [[Linux DE prototyping|projects.linux-desktop]]\n- [[System Archaeology|projects.system-archaeology]]\n\n---\n\n![](/assets/images/2021-03-18-20-55-10.png)\n\n[El Lissitzky, The Constructor (self-portrait, 1924)](https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:El_Lissitzky_The_Constructor,_self-portrait,_gelatin_silver_print,_107%C3%97118_mm,_1924_London,_Victoria_and_Albert_Museum,_Inv._PH142-1985.jpg)\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2